<TEXT>
tropical chocolate a 
synthetic that tastes like the real thing but wont melt in the 
heat could be ready for shipment to the persian gulf in time for 
the holidays 
the allelectric tank wont be 
military historians are fond of saying that generals are forever 
fighting the last war the army materiel command has the job of 
making sure that doesnt happen 
the amc which is responsible for research and development of 
gear used by the army is playing host this week to an exposition 
of what the future may hold for the nations warriors 
the soldier in the field is our customer said edward brown 
civilian deputy director of the amc office of technology management 
and planning 
the projects presented at this base 30 miles north of baltimore 
are in various stages of development from a wild idea to a 
concept on the verge of production 
the allelectric tank which would use batteries or 
superconducting technology is one of those projects way off in the 
future 
taken as a whole the projects represent the beginning of a 
shift from a neartotal preoccupation with the soviet threat to a 
realization the nation could face a myriad of military challenges 
in coming years 
the buzzword we use these days is that instead of weapons of 
mass destruction were looking to produce weapons of mass 
disruption said brown 
the object said brown is to create a smaller leaner but more 
effective force that can fight a smallscale war in a jungle as 
well as it could a major tank battle in central europe 
to that end the army and its scientists are pushing against the 
frontiers of science 
in laboratories across the country researchers are looking for 
military applications for the next generation of supercomputers and 
trying to harness recent breakthroughs in magnetics and 
superconductors 
they are working with corporations and universities on new 
fabrics to improve uniforms new materials to enhance tanks and 
personnel carriers and robots to reduce the danger to soldiers 
the scientists and managers gathered here envision an army in 
which the soldier has enhanced survivability and enhanced 
lethality 
in the next century the gi on patrol may carry his own computer 
along with tastier rations he may be wearing a selfcontained 
airconditioned uniform to protect him from the heat as well as 
chemical weapons 
generals will be able to rely on computers that produce 
corpslevel battle plans in 40 minutes a task that now takes at 
least a day 
and those computers will be able to give commanders a range of 
options and tell them when a battle plan isnt working and suggest 
appropriate responses 
officers will brief their troops using tv screens instead of 
pointers and paper maps on easels 
the technology expo is designed to spark new ideas as well as 
sell the nation on the importance of such work in an era of budget 
cuts 
the decision was very specifically made to keep the rampd as 
high as possible because thats the seed corn brown said 
thats the future were going to push the technology 
</TEXT>
