<TEXT>
nearly 40 percent of the nations minority students and about 30 
percent of its poor children are educated in large urban school 
districts according to data collected by the council of great city 
schools 
about 11 percent or 45 million us schoolchildren attend 
school in the nations 37 largest urban districts according to the 
council 
urban districts with the biggest enrollments are new york 
940000 los angeles 592000 chicago 394000 miamidade county 
fla 268000 philadelphia 191000 houston 190000 detroit 
174000 dallas 131000 san diego 117000 baltimore 107000 
and memphis tenn 106000 
the families of nearly 15 million urban schoolchildren are 
below the poverty line 408000 are enrolled in classes for the 
handicapped 293000 have limited english proficiency 
fortyfive percent are black 26 percent white 23 percent 
hispanic and 5 percent asian 
daily attendance averages 94 percent in urban elementary 
schools 91 percent in middle schools and 876 percent in high 
schools the national average for all schools is 92 percent 
excluding federal funds and capital spending pittsburgh spent 
the most per pupil among the 50 largest school districts 7163 
according to 198889 data from the american federation of teachers 
the latest comparable statistics available memphis tenn at 
2521 spent the least the 50district average was 4365 
average class size in the the 50 largest us districts is about 
17 students compared with the 174 average for the entire nation 
according to aft statistics 
newark nj had the best pupilteacher ratio 115 followed 
by st louis 124 boston 126 baltimore county 135 
pittsburgh 140 orange county orlando fla 145 denver 145 
and columbus ohio 145 los angeles had the most crowded classes 
among the 50 largest districts with a studentteacher ratio of 24 
some 203000 teachers work in innercity schools 
among urban districts with settled contracts in 199091 
philadelphia teachers earn from 24000 to 49600 newark 
teachers 23867 to 50757 minneapolis teachers 22192 to 
47273 cincinnati teachers 21679 to 44847 baltimore 
teachers 22162 to 43002 and dade county fla teachers 
26500 to 49400 
</TEXT>
