yosemite national park 
celebrates its 100th birthday monday hundreds of millions of years 
after the formation of the sierra nevada that glaciers later carved 
into majestic valleys 
the 748542acre park was created by congress on oct 1 1890 
26 years after the federal government gave yosemite valley to 
california for use as a public park and recreation area the park 
is about 130 miles east of san francisco 
john muir a naturalist first saw the area in the 1860s and his 
enthusiastic reports help spark interest in preserving yosemite 
now some 34 million people visit the park each year 
during the past century yosemite has seen controversies and 
disasters development interests and concessionaires have battled 
environmentalists about how much to build in the park this summer 
a fire raged through yosemite closing the valley for 11 days and 
burning 23000 acres 
but the park that includes el capitan half dome yosemite falls 
one of the worlds tallest waterfalls has survived its granite 
rock faces and tall trees reaching ever upward 
we believe weve seen 100 years of preservation and were 
working hard to ensure that the next 100 years are even going to be 
better for the visitors and the park said yosemite 
superintendent michael finley 
a ceremony marking the milestone will be held monday 
the sierra was created hundreds of millions of years ago when 
the earths plates collided according to generally accepted 
scientific theory ice ages then came unleashing glaciers tens of 
thousands of years ago 
