<TEXT>
as much of the world retreats from communism 
chinese premier li peng has toasted the partys 41year rule with 
praise for its great glorious and correct leadership 
li also lauded the army and police for their roles in 
controlling dissent and implementing new anticrime measures 
li made the toast sunday at an annual reception for foreign 
diplomats on the eve of the anniversary of the 1949 birth of the 
peoples republic of china following the overthrow of the 
nationalist government 
athletes from chinas asian games team also attended and mingled 
with the top leaders who begged for autographs the 36nation 
games are under way in beijing and scheduled to close oct 7 
the communist party turned an impoverished backward old china 
which was subjected to the bullying and enslavement by colonialism 
and imperialism into a socialist new china with initial 
prosperity li said in his 15minute toast 
the communist party of china is a great glorious and correct 
party we have every ability to manage our own affairs well and 
socialist china has a bright future full of infinite promise he 
said 
chinese leaders maintain that the collapse of socialism in 
eastern europe is only a temporary setback and capitalism will 
eventually fail since putting down a prodemocracy movement in 
1989 chinese officials have kept tight controls on any dissent and 
filled the official media with praise of the party 
the premiers annual national day toast serves as an abridged 
stateofthenation address summarizing chinas political and 
economic situation and the basic domestic and foreign policies 
this years toast contained no surprises reaffirming the 
governments determination to maintain a planned economy 
li said the government was intensifying efforts to complete a 
new fiveyear plan for submission to the party central committee 
he gave no explanation for the plans delay believed to be the 
result of sharp disagreement over resuming marketstyle economic 
reforms the new plan is due to take effect in january 
li praised an anticrime campaign that has resulted in more than 
650 death sentences being handed down from january to august 
according to the human rights group amnesty international 
in an unusual move party general secretary jiang zemin attended 
the reception held in the great hall of the people the annual 
event generally is considered a state affair rather than a party 
function 
the exiled leader of cambodias rebel resistance prince norodom 
sihanouk also attended and sat between jiang and li 
