the cruzans visit their daughter weekly at the staterun 
missouri rehabilitation center in mount vernon her body is rigid 
her hands and feet bent into claws she breathes on her own and at 
times her eyes are open and move randomly 
the legal fight began when the parents after realizing their 
daughter would never recover asked doctors to remove the feeding 
tube the doctors refused and in 1987 the family went to teel 
teel ruled for the family in 1988 the missouri supreme court 
overturned that decision five months later the family appealed to 
the us supreme court 
ms cruzan left no written instructions about what she would 
want done under such circumstances the family however had 
testified they were certain about their request based on a 
lifetime of experiences and conversations the young woman had with 
a friend 
the cruzans said three people they wont identify have now come 
forward to say that their daughter had expressed a wish not to be 
kept alive in such fashion 
bill colby an attorney for ms cruzan and her family said the 
new evidence meets the clear and convincing standard 
the attorney general meanwhile said he has asked teel to hold 
a hearing on removing the state health department from the 
litigation the department runs the rehabilitation center no 
hearing date has been set 
</TEXT>
