smiths suit against mcdonald went all the way to the nations 
highest court before it ever reached a trial 
in 1985 the supreme court justices used the case to rule that 
people may be sued over allegedly libelous statements made in 
letters and petitions to government officials the decision said 
the first amendment right to petition the government did not cloak 
mcdonald in absolute immunity from being sued over what he said 
about smith 
