reduced if dialogue replaces the policy of threats and warnings 
if the language of peaceful politics replaces the policy of troop 
buildups and threats of the use of force 
however he again linked any solution to an israeli pullout from 
the occupied territories and he said iraq would defend kuwait if 
necessary 
saddam said he wanted to open a dialogue with france to explore 
the possibility of using president francois mitterrands ideas on 
negotiating a broad middle east peace as basis for a settlement 
he said he viewed mitterrands proposals as being of a 
different language than past foreign denunciations of iraq 
adding we hope our positive interpretation is correct 
in a un speech on sept 24 mitterrand suggested settling the 
