<TEXT>
the us supreme court hears arguments 
tuesday in a case that could define the federal judiciarys duties 
and responsibilities after a school system is declared 
desegregated 
in the long run up to 500 school districts nationwide could be 
affected by the high courts decision say lawyers for both sides 
in the case its not known when the court will rule 
the question before the court is whether the oklahoma city 
school boards 1985 decision to abandon forced busing will lead the 
district away from a desegregated or unitary system 
us district judge luther bohanon ruled in 1985 that the 
federal court could not intervene to stop the boards neighborhood 
school plan which abandoned forced busing for students in 
kindergarten through fourth grades students in upper grades are 
still bused 
bohanon reasoned that since he had declared the oklahoma city 
district desegregated in 1977 the federal courts no longer had 
jurisdiction 
the naacp appealed and the 10th us circuit court of appeals 
reversed bohanon the school district appealed to the supreme 
court 
the 10th circuit said federal court supervision in such cases 
extends beyond the termination of the wrongdoing it said the 
oklahoma city school board had a continuing duty to refrain from 
any action that would weaken racial balance in the public schools 
and ordered bohanon to study alternatives to maintain racially 
balanced elementary schools 
school superintendent arthur stellar maintains that no 
segregation results from the neighborhood school plan 
steller said there are no identifiably white schools left in the 
district but admits that 10 of the 58 elementary schools are 90 
percent or more black 
he blamed that on the fact that the neighborhoods are not 
entirely integrated but he added if the present trends 
continue they would become more and more integrated 
i think ideally we would live in a world where schools 
churches and neighborhoods would all be integrated unfortunately 
thats not the situation in which we live steller said 
not everyone agrees the system is desegregated 
we have 32 elementary schools in oklahoma city that are 
racially identifiable and by racially identifiable i mean 90 to 98 
percent one race or the other said roosevelt milton president 
of the local chapter of the national association for the 
advancement of colored people 
milton said the neighborhood plan has shortchanged blacks 
id say essentially were getting inexperienced educators and 
a lack of adequate books and supplies and i think relegating a 
very high number of socioeconomically deprived students into the 
same school he said 
the case has spanned nearly three decades 
in october 1961 al dowell a black optometrist filed a 
lawsuit contending his son robert was denied admission to a 
predominantly white high school he alleged a quota system was used 
to keep black enrollment at predominantly white schools to a 
minimum and that there was a double standard for the two races 
nearly two years later bohanon ordered the district to take 
extensive steps to bring racial balance to the schools in the 
197273 school year courtordered busing began and thousands of 
children were transported throughout a district where only 251 
percent of the students were black and 749 percent were white 
about 5000 children rode school buses before bohanons 1972 
busing order that number jumped by 15000 for the 197273 school 
year according to minutes from school board meetings 
many whites left the school district for the suburbs from an 
enrollment of 68904 in 1971 the district dropped to 59241 the 
next year it was down to only 37735 pupils in the school year 
just completed 
white students were the minority last year 447 percent of the 
total enrollment black enrollment was up to 40 percent while the 
remaining 153 percent was listed as spanish american indian or 
oriental 
six years after the forced busing began bohanon ruled that it 
had achieved its objective he declared the oklahoma city school 
district to be desegregated and ended court supervision 
school officials continued the busing until the 198586 school 
term when the neighborhood school concept was implemented 
</TEXT>
