<TEXT>
father sergio giuramondos quest for inner peace 
provides the drama on screen in the taviani brothers night 
sun off screen finding the actor to play father sergio was an 
equally difficult task 
we had an image in our head and we couldnt find someone in 
italy or in france said paulo taviani in a press conference with 
brother vittorio after the films recent screening at the new york 
film festival one day we saw a picture of english actor 
julian sands and just from his face his body we thought he would 
be right 
we met with him for a long time we had him read parts from 
other films of ours it was a little difficult at first not to have 
an actor whos italian but its happened many many times perhaps 
because we belong to an underdeveloped country that has to borrow 
bits of culture from others joked paulo whose previous films 
with vittorio include the night of san lorenzo and good 
morning babylon 
night sun is based on father sergio a short novel by 
leo tolstoy and takes place in 18thcentury naples the original 
story was based in 19th century st petersburg 
as a boy the intense sergio wishes to serve his king and 
eventually receives his wish but the king pushes him into a 
disastrous engagement with the beautiful cristina nastassja 
kinski who reveals that for a year she was the monarchs 
mistress 
an enraged sergio storms out of her home and decides to become a 
monk the monastery also proves unsatisfactory too close to the 
temptations of the secular world and sergio chooses to become a 
hermit 
even then his will is tested he is twice visited by women who 
desire him sexually and receives unwanted fame when villagers 
believe he is responsible for making a dumb boy speak the film 
ends with sergio wandering from village to village 
the film centers on the predicament of ones desire for 
privacy and ones desire to interact with others explained 
vittorio taviani 
a constant was a desire to tell a beautiful story added 
paulo the most important stories such as the iliad often 
have a journey as their theme 
night sun runs for 112 minutes and does not have an american 
distributor 
the new york film festival opened sept 21 with millers 
crossing and closes oct 7 with the nasty girl 
