<TEXT>
the norwegian nobel institute and the 
countrys news media are in the throes of a guessing game with 
traditions as strong as the peace prize itself 
the ritual is simple norways press tries to guess the name of 
the annual nobel laureate and the institute says nothing even 
though the decision was probably made several months ago 
we never say who the winner is before the official 
announcement said institute director geir lundestad there are 
100 nominations including 26 organizations for the 71st peace 
prize he said the winner will be announced oct 15 in oslo 
the other nobel prizes will be announced in stockholm starting 
with medicine on oct 8 the economics prize established in 1968 
and funded by the bank of sweden will be announced oct 16 
physics and chemistry prizes funded by income from the will of 
dynamiteinventor alfred bernard nobel will be announced oct 17 
the date for the literature prize has not been announced 
this years prizes are worth 695000 
there is an opportunity for one more meeting but most of the 
pieces have fallen into place lundestad said when asked if a 
1990 peace prize winner had been selected 
the media has picked four hot names soviet president mikhail s 
gorbachev african national congress deputy president nelson 
mandela chinese prodemocracy student leader chai ling and 
czechoslovak president vaclev havel 
