leader of tibet had probably already been selected 
other recent winners were lech walesa leader of polands 
solidarity union south african anglican archbishop desmond tutu 
mother teresa and the united nations peace keeping forces 
lundestad said the great secrecy about the coveted prize first 
awarded in 1901 protects some candidates from reprisals or keeps 
their activities confidential 
names of candidates are never released no notes leave the room 
after deliberations by the fivemember nobel peace prize committee 
appointed by norways parliament for sixyear terms 
but nominations are often announced by those forwarding a 
candidate 
there are thousands of people and organizations with the right 
to nominate including former laureates elected officials even 
some university professors and organizations said lundestad who 
is not a voting member of the committee 
the picture becomes more clouded by scores of nominations from 
groups who have no right to make them norways largest labor 
union for example announced its enthusiastic but invalid 
nomination of gorbachev 
in that particular case the name was also forwarded in 
several other valid nominations lundestad said he confirmed the 
nomination because several groups have announced it 
the fiveemployee institute sifts through thousands of letters a 
year hunting for valid nominations that arrived before the feb 1 
deadline 
the us chamber of commerce this year pushed for the award in a 
secret campaign that appears to have started after a winner had 
already been selected 
it doesnt do any good anyway lundestad said about such 
campaigns 
the fiercely independent committee aided by institute 
researchers searches for a person or group fulfilling criteria set 
in nobels will 
there have been 19 years in which no prize was awarded 
