the gray doors of a prison swung open monday 
and karsten petermann strolled into the sunlight a free man in a 
free land for the first time in his life 
its a new chance petermann 21 said as he walked through 
the massive steel gate of east berlins highsecurity rummelsburg 
prison 
petermann was among the first convicts freed after the east 
german parliament in one of its last official acts before german 
unity on wednesday adopted a broad amnesty plan for people behind 
bars 
the program meant to make up for the harsh sentences handed 
down by the former communist regime trims prison sentences by a 
third for all inmates who were not convicted of violent crimes 
it was also a bit of a shock for inmates who were released not 
only into a newly democratic east germany but one that is two days 
from being absorbed by west germany 
sven heyse 20 served 13 months of a 20month sentence he said 
was handed down because he stoe 50 east german marks from his 
sisters boyfriend that cash was the equivalent of about 20 west 
german marks 12 under the former official exchange rate 
we lived in an oppressive land and we could never have 
expected this kind of amnesty from the communists under honecker 
and mielke he said referring to ousted communist party boss 
erich honecker and the chief of his secret police erich mielke 
