<TEXT>
indias supreme court ordered the 
government on monday to halt its controversial job quota program 
and appealed for an end to protests against the policy that have 
killed dozens of people 
we hope that the law and order situation will immediately 
improve chief justice ranganath mishra said after issuing the 
ruling 
the courts temporary injunction remains in effect until the 
panel rules on the legality of the quotas press trust of india 
said the court could begin to hear arguments on the affirmative 
action program as early as oct 25 
at least 70 people have died in a rash of riots and student 
suicides since prime minister vp singh announced aug 7 that 
almost half of all government jobs would be reserved for 
lowercaste hindus 
public opposition to the governmen has been widespread in the 
politically influential cities of northern india the army has been 
called out and curfews clamped on several towns to control rioting 
students joined sometimes by middleaged housewives and government 
employees 
two members of singhs governing party have resigned from 
parliament and some colleagues demanded his ouster because of the 
quotas singh has refused to abandon the policy saying it is an 
affirmative action program that would give social justice to the 
lower castes 
critics say he fears alienating the lower castes which form a 
majority of the eligible votes among indias 880 million people 
uppercaste students say reverse discrimination will deprive 
them of government jobs for which they are better qualified 
on monday the decision was taken out of singhs hands 
the supreme court said the government should take no action on 
the policys implementation until its legality is determined 
until the matter is heard and we expect it to be finished 
before the end of the year no further steps should be taken 
mishra said 
the court however allowed the government to continue 
assembling a list of the thousands of castes that will qualify for 
the job quotas 
the plan reserves 27 percent of federal jobs for lowcaste 
hindus an additional 22 percent already are set aside for the 
lowest strata in the rigid hierarchy of indian society 
tribespeople and the socalled untouchables 
in parliament the government faced a separate problem monday 
when it failed to pass a constitutional amendment extending federal 
rule in the northern state of punjab where sikh militants are 
fighting for independence 
the state govenment in punjab was dismissed in 1987 and replaced 
by federal rule which the constitution limits to three years 
amending the document requires a twothirds majority 
in a surprise move aimed at embarassing the government the 
opposition congress party refused to support the bill leaders of 
all the parties were summoned to the speakers chambers to find a 
way out of the impasse 
singh 10monthold government suffered another setback when the 
speaker of the legislature agreed to hold a debate on a motion 
seeking to censure the government for mishandling the student 
protest 
the motion if passed would put pressure on the government to 
quit said kewal verma a parliamentary analyst 
there is no legal obligation on the part of the government to 
resign but it would amount to its defeat in moral terms verma 
said 
in the parliament congress party members accused singh of being 
obstinate for refusing to suspend or reconsider the affirmative 
action plan down down resign resign they shouted as singh 
stood up to speak he was prevented from addressing the house 
cant you see there is blood in your hands said congress 
lawmaker ajit panja some members advanced menacingly at singh but 
were stopped by colleagues you are a bloodstained politician 
panja said 
former congress minister vasant sathe said he was beginning a 
fast unto death until singh stops police terror on the 
students 
in the northern town of jammu 17yearold student sandeep 
sharma set himself on fire monday in the latest suicide bid to 
protest the job quotas he suffered thirddegree burns over most of 
his body 
at least 20 students have died in the past 12 days from 
selfinflicted injuries most left notes blaming singhs job 
policy in addition 50 people have died by police gunfire in 
street battles 
