at issue is whether a federal law the veterans reemployment 
rights act gives employees an absolute right to join the reserves 
and an absolute entitlement to a leave of absence to fulfill 
reserve training obligations 
the 4th us circuit court of appeals last march ruled in the 
baltimore case that employers never may interfere with a workers 
joining or serving in the reserves 
other federal courts however have said employers need not 
honor an employees request for a leave to serve in the reserves if 
the request is not reasonable 
lawyers for the baltimore police department urged the justices 
to resolve the conflicting rulings 
