<TEXT>
an earthquake of moderate intensity 
shook houses and buildings across puerto rico on monday but there 
were no reports of injuries or damage 
the quake registered 45 on the richter scale and was centered 
near the coastal city of humacao 30 miles southeast of san juan 
according to the us geological survey in golden colo 
the seismological survey in cayey puerto rico said the temblor 
struck at 236 pm edt lasted five seconds and was felt as far 
away as st john in the us virgin islands 50 miles east of 
puerto rico 
it was strongest in puerto rico particularly the san juan 
metropolitan area said allan smith director of the seismological 
network of puerto rico at the university of mayaguez 
he said there were no reports of damage or injuries but the 
quake prompted a flurry of telephone calls to television and radio 
stations 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph 
an earthquake of 4 on the richter scale can cause moderate 
damage while a 5 can cause considerable damage 
