and adopted by the full senate in its version of the defense bill 
in august 
although he originally proposed 307 billion in military 
spending back in january bush accepted the 289 billion amount in 
a speech this summer and the white house has endorsed the figure 
the house last month approved a 283 billion defense bill that 
would slash more than 2 billion from the strategic defense 
initiative halt production of the b2 bomber and cut troop 
strength by 129500 
the senate legislation would cut 1 billion from the sdi budget 
and reduce us troop strength by 100000 but leave the b2 stealth 
bomber program intact 
i think the defense numbers are reasonable and i certainly can 
support those nunn said of the negotiators agreement in an 
interview monday 
members of the house and senate planned to meet tuesday to begin 
crafting a final defense package for fiscal 1991 from their two 
widely divergent bills 
house democrats and republicans on the armed services committee 
expressed the hope that lawmakers in their chamber would not give 
in to the senate and the administration 
i really hope we dont retreat and stand our ground at 283 
billion said rep larry hopkins rky who envisioned lawmakers 
adding 6 billion of their pet projects to reach the higher number 
they dont ever have any trouble ratcheting up theyll find a 
good cause hopkins said 
lawmakers also expressed concern over the absence of the cost of 
operation desert shield the us military deployment in the 
persian gulf from the budget compromise 
defense secretary dick cheney has estimated that the buildup 
could cost about 15 billion in fiscal 1991 
schroeder suggested that the 6 billion difference between the 
house and senate numbers could be used for operation desert shield 
