<TEXT>
the four victorious powers of world war ii 
decided monday to suspend their rights over berlin and germany 
allowing the divided nation to become fully sovereign from the 
moment of reunification this week 
foreign ministers of the united states soviet union britain 
and france signed a document suspending operation of the rights 
they have exercised in germany since the war ended in 1945 
the rights will formally terminate when all four powers have 
ratified a sept 12 moscow treaty that paved the way for 
reunification wednesday 
those strokes of a pen bring to an end an era of discord and 
division said president bush at the opening of a twoday 
35nation conference on security and cooperation in europe 
we rejoice with the german people that their nation is united 
once more and we will soon welcome a united germany into the 
conferences community of states bush said 
the conference is an outgrowth of the 1975 helsinki conference 
on european security that the nations intend to use as a framework 
for cooperation in the postcold war era 
we are uniting in happiness and gratitude not in 
nationalistic exhuberance said west german foreign minister 
hansdietrich genscher the dark chapters of our history are a 
cause for reflection on what was done in germanys name that 
will not be repeated 
