<TEXT>
the texas railroad commission voted 21 monday 
against raising oil production in the east texas field by 8000 to 
15000 barrels a day one commissioner said the extra oil isnt 
needed despite the persian gulf crisis 
there is no shortage of oil on the market any more the 
only thing hiking the price of oil is the new york mercantile 
exchange based on rumor said commissioner john sharp 
sharp and commissioner jim nugent outvoted chairman kent hance 
in keeping the east texas field production at 86 percent the us 
energy department had asked the commission to increase production 
to help offset oil lost due to the iraqi invasion of kuwait 
the commission in august voted to allow the production of about 
20000 more barrels of oil per day from wells outside the east 
texas field most of the higher production is coming from fields in 
the austin chalk in south texas 
all of the oil that was stopped from kuwait and iraq has been 
replaced either domestically by venezuela or by saudi arabia 
sharp said 
according to the railroad commission the state produced 178 
million barrels of oil a day last year down from 336 million a 
day in 1974 and 255 million a day in 1980 
many independent oil producers in east texas opposed the 
production incrnglish husband an americanized version of the british film 
