<TEXT>
oil minister hisham nazer expressed 
concern about spiraling oil prices on monday and said saudi arabia 
would continue to increase production 
the kingdom has raised its own output by more than 2 million 
barrels per day to help remedy the situation and will increase 
its output at close intervals in the near future nazer was 
quoted as saying before the weekly session of the saudi government 
chaired by king fahd 
there is no need whatsoever for panic to spread in the market 
since consumption in the fourth quarter of the year is estimated at 
545 million barrels per day with various sources capable of 
providing 53 million barrels per day information minister ali 
alshaer quoted nazer as saying in a report on the cabinet session 
to the saudi press agency 
the remainder would be no more than 15 million barrels per 
day or 2 million at most and that can be withdrawn from the 
commercial stockpiles which are estimated at 700 million barrels at 
present nazer said 
since iraq invaded kuwait the price of oil has reached as high 
as 41 dollars a barrel for brent crude and 37 for dubai crude 
nazer warned that the effects of such increases if they continue 
to escalate will be grave for both developing as well as 
industrialized countries 
he recalled the special meeting of the organization of petroleum 
exporting countries at the outset of the gulf crisis when prices 
were 2750 per barrel for brent and 25 for dubai 
it was a price far beyond what the market could absorb 
economically or be borne by the developing nations he said 
with the aug 2 invasion the market suffered a shortfall of 45 
million barrels per day that the two countries used to export 
nazer noted that saudi arabia the worlds largest oil exporter 
had raised its oil by more than 2 million barrels a day 
the kingdom is using the best industrialized techniques in its 
production he said and will increase that output at close 
intervals in the near future without affecting its oil fields 
the statement was an apparent denial of reports that saudi 
arabia might not be able to maintain its output of 75 million 
barrels per day because of technical difficulties 
